cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the parallelization of computation of convolutional neural networks. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with parallelization across multiple GPUs. It could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as convolutional neural networks are a popular technique in these fields.
